            <thetext>Currently, the anchor is positioned with negative/positive margins and floated to take it out of normal flow. This can be improved, for instance by positioning relative to the containing block which is better to maintain and easier to implement.

Because of bug 5961 (see section 3), Firefox enlarges the containing block by the border-box width of the anchor. When using relative positioning as outlined above, this browser bug can be avoided.</thetext>
